  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operation manager",
  "description": "<p>Job Responsibilities</p><p>Responsible for the daily operation and management of the company's food manufacturing and catering-related businesses, ensuring smooth and efficient production and operation processes.</p><p>Supervise food production, processing, packaging, and distribution processes to ensure compliance with SFA and relevant food safety and hygiene regulations.</p><p>Develop and implement operational plans, production schedules, and resource allocation to improve production efficiency and control costs.</p><p>Manage and train the operations team, including production, warehousing, and logistics personnel.</p><p>Monitor inventory, raw material procurement, and supply chain operations to ensure sufficient materials and reduce waste.</p><p>Work closely with management to regularly report operational performance, issues, and improvement suggestions.</p><p>Handle unexpected operational issues to ensure business continuity and customer satisfaction.</p><p>Ensure the workplace meets safety, hygiene, and internal company policy requirements.</p><p></p><p>Job Requirements</p><p>At least 3 years of operational management experience in the catering, food manufacturing, or related industries.</p><p>Familiar with food manufacturing processes and food safety standards (such as SFA, HACCP). (Preference will be given to candidates with relevant experience)</p><p>Possesses excellent team management, communication, and organizational skills.</p><p>Able to independently plan and execute operational plans, and has problem-solving abilities.</p><p>Possesses cost control and basic data analysis skills.</p><p>Able to work efficiently in a fast-paced and high-pressure work environment.</p><p>Proficient in basic office software (Microsoft Office, etc.).</p><p>Preference will be given to candidates with relevant industry experience in Singapore.</p>",
